description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit a dynamic and enthusiastic Band 6 CAMHS Practitioner who is passionate about working with Children and young people with Neurodevelopmental conditions such as ADHD, ASD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a clinical position, working with young people with a neurodevelopmental diagnosis, mental health problems and challenging behaviours. You will also work closely with their families, carers, and professional networks, as well as being supported by a dedicated team of professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role will include contributing to assessment (semi-structured clinical, neuropsychological, structured diagnostic assessment, observation) reviewing and assessing children and young people who require stimulant medication. Formulation and intervention (including direct individual, family, group therapeutic work, psychoeducation, indirect behavioural work, case management and post diagnostic support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be required to support the team in terms of ensuring smooth running and organisation of the service, research, evaluation, and service development as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work within a clinic setting as well as community, although during this period, a large amount of clinical work is carried out virtually via Attend Anywhere and Teams. You will be able to access regular individual supervision, peer supervision, CPD opportunities within and outside of the service and will be well support to develop your career within a caring supportive team environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are challenging but exciting times to join the team, as we move forward into new ways of working, if you’re ready to make a positive change we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is full-time although we would would be willing to consider to part-time hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that there is a relocation bonus available to this post.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The permanent posts are eligible for a £1500 New Hire Bonus. An initial payment of £500 will be paid in the first 1 month and a final payment of £1000 will be paid 1 year after your start date. This will be pro-rata for part-time posts. Internal applicants are not eligible.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gemma Balnaves, Interim Service Manager CAMHS Core/Neuro Central Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;gemma.balnaves@cpft.nhs.uk / 01480 445281&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
